Proposed (25.6s): Use this skill for ANY question, code, or debugging involving the Agent Execution Protocol (AEP) — a wire format between agent runners (which drive an LLM and emit events) and supervisors (which declare the environment via a Config).

Trigger when the user names AEP, OR uses AEP-specific terms without saying "AEP": `Config` with `tools`/`verifiers`/`re_observation`/`boundary`, events like `tool_exec_request`/`tool_exec_resolved`/`re_observation_request`/`re_observation_resolved`/`verifier_evaluated`/`agent_stopped`, fields like `on_failure: halt|inject_correction|continue`, `source: { runner|supervisor }`, `call_id`, `RunStateSnapshot`, the v0.1 spec, §10.4, conformance cases, or imports of `aep`/`aep_anthropic`/`aep_claude_agent`.

Trigger for: writing/wrapping a runner over any LLM SDK; authoring or reviewing a supervisor Config; verifiers as invariants; cache-token accounting; boundary semantics; conformance tests; and any "why is my AEP run/Config/verifier doing X?" debugging.

Do NOT trigger for: generic agent observability, OpenTelemetry, prompt engineering, LLM cost dashboards, or unrelated agent frameworks where AEP is not the protocol.

